<i>noun</i>: 추모 [추모], 추도 [추도], 애도 [애도], 상복 [상복] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>추모 [추모]</dt><br>
<dd>mourning; missing the deceased</dd><br>
<dd>죽은 사람을 생각하고 그리워함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of thinking about and missing the deceased.</dd><br>
<dt>추도 [추도]</dt><br>
<dd>mourning; remembrance</dd><br>
<dd>죽은 사람을 생각하며 슬퍼함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of mourning, remembering a dead person.</dd><br>
<dt>애도 [애도]</dt><br>
<dd>grief; mourning; condolence</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 죽음을 슬퍼함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of mourning someone's death.</dd><br>
<dt>상복 [상복]</dt><br>
<dd>mourning; mourning clothes</dd><br>
<dd>삼베로 만들거나 검정색 또는 흰색으로 되어 상중인 사람이 입는 옷.</dd><br>
<dd>A dress made of hemp fabric, or colored in black or white that one wears during the period of mourning.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>